It seems to me that the number one priority on loot is: How much is this item needed by the guild?<br>
<br>
Basically, I've always thought that (in a group) the person who NEEDS the item should have first priority..as the advancement of that person's equipment is part of advancing the guild. For example: (not that this would ever happen, but for the purposes of illustration...) 5 warriors and a wizard are camping the AM....who gets the robe? well...the wizard of course...UNLESS...(and this brings me to scenario #2:<br>
<br>
No one in the group needs the item.....in that case, I'm of the opinion that the group as a whole should decide (vote) on which guild member should recieve said item....as Keke and I have done 2 or 3 times with some Bladed Thulian Claws...This seems to work well...and also benefits the guild as a whole. Then we have scenario number 3:<br>
<br>
No one in the group wants the item...no one in the guild needs the item.....in that case...roll on it...and let the winner do with it as he or she sees fit. This includes giving the item to an Alt. character....<br>
<br>
Hate to say it...but in order to focus on our goals...alt characters are at the VERY BOTTOM of the ladder when it comes to loot.<br>
<br>
All of the above aplies mostly to full claw groups...obviously, if a non-member is in the group...you'll roll for it....in which case...you won the item (if you won...) and may do with it as you wish...after all..we are not in full claw groups ALL the time..<br>
<br>
I'm sure I left out MANY crucial details...as I've had no sleep...so please feel free to respond...point out whatever I've overlooked...let's get a solid discussion going on this topic...so we can have a loot plan that is &quot;set in stone&quot;<br>
